, 80 mm TL estimated, Ilha dos Frades, 
<normalizedToken id="4913CCF47CC940EFE487D5BAA7A81A6D" originalValue="Baía">Baia</normalizedToken>
de Todos os Santos, Bahia, Brazil. Photograph by 
<normalizedToken id="DA33E96FB11FC00FD534A9402631B24F" originalValue="Cláudio">Claudio</normalizedToken>
L. S. Sampaio.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="8B6E37BFE607553EA247691C52E99DE3" pageId="17" pageNumber="112">
<paragraph id="DCA13BA7B37E14FDFCCFE66B1E95AD52" pageId="17" pageNumber="112">
Figure 15. 
<taxonomicName id="457C384E73CD2569442752084B34C824" class="Actinopterygii" family="Opistognathidae" genus="Opistognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opistognathus cuvierii" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="112" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cuvierii">Opistognathus cuvierii</taxonomicName>
, SU 52354, 102 mm SL, male, Bahia, Brazil. Drawn by Jack R. Schroeder; after 
<bibRefCitation id="3958FADFA28746E78BAF55A57C854EBA" author="Smith-Vaniz, WF" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" pagination="1074 - 1128" title="Descriptions of five new species of jawfishes (Opistognathus: Opistognathidae) from the western Atlantic Ocean." volume="60" year="1997">Smith-Vaniz (1997)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
